oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Oche Finceco
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Portrait of Oche-Finceco with ruffled white collar and blue tunic with red fringes.

Oche-Finceco, called Charles Cornells. He was one of the Creek delegation and signers of the Treaty of Washington in 1826. Not much else is known of Oche-Finceco except that he committed suicide after signing the treaty.
